# Mastering Logical Operators

Combine multiple conditions with logical operators to create complex decision-making logic!

## The Three Logical Operators

### AND (&&) - Both must be true
```csharp
int level = 10;
int gold = 500;

if (level >= 10 && gold >= 300)
{
    Console.WriteLine("You can enter the elite dungeon!");
}
```

### OR (||) - At least one must be true
```csharp
string role = "Mage";
int intelligence = 15;

if (role == "Mage" || intelligence >= 20)
{
    Console.WriteLine("You can cast magic!");
}
```

### NOT (!) - Inverts a boolean
```csharp
bool hasKey = false;

if (!hasKey)
{
    Console.WriteLine("You need a key to open this door!");
}
```

## Combining Operators

```csharp
int health = 50;
int mana = 20;
bool inCombat = true;

if ((health > 30 && mana > 10) || !inCombat)
{
    Console.WriteLine("You can cast a spell!");
}
```

## Your Quest

Create an advanced quest eligibility checker:
1. Get player level, gold, and whether they have a guild membership
2. Check multiple quest eligibilities:
   - **Epic Quest**: Level >= 15 AND Gold >= 1000
   - **Guild Quest**: Has guild membership OR Level >= 20
   - **Starter Quest**: Level < 5 AND Gold < 100
   - **Any Quest**: NOT in combat (always true for now)
3. Display which quests they're eligible for

